<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4545116>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Fig. 30. Live views of Micronycteris homezi (AMNH 267414; male). Note the pale ventral fur, the long hairs on the leading edge of each pinna, and the very deep, V­shaped notch in the interauricular band; the cutaneous fossa is visible through the notch in the interauricular band. The hairs covering the fossa in this view are rooted in the skin surrounding the fossa, and on the underside (posterior surface) of the interauricular band; the fossa itself is hairless." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4545116/files/figure.png" .

